(CNN) An Israeli flight attendant has slipped into a coma after contracting measles, according to health officials.
The flight attendant, who works for El Al, the Israeli national airline, might have contracted the virus in New York, in Israel or on a flight between the two, Grotto said.
Ongoing measles outbreaks in the United States and Israel started with parents who've chosen not to vaccinate their children, according to health authorities.
One dose of vaccine not optimalLike many others of her generation around the world, the flight attendant, who has not been identified, received only one dose of the measles vaccine when she was a child.
Ukraine has had more than 72,000 measles cases this year, more than any other country, according to the World Health OrganizationAbout 85% to 90% of Israeli measles cases have been among ultra-Orthodox Jews, Grotto said.